main event: On 5 November 1957 in Walworth, Wisconsin, a civilian observed a small, round object with red and white lights, moving up and down low in the sky for 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as small, round, with red and white lights that flashed on and off.
It was observed moving up and down in the sky, with no discernible features like a trail or tail of exhaust, and no sound.
The report concluded that it was likely a weather balloon, citing the descriptive elements of the observation that matched a balloon with lights attached.
No photographs or material evidence of the sighting were provided.
The weather conditions at the time of the sighting were described as having scattered clouds, calm winds at the surface, and no unusual activity in the area.
sighted object: small, round object with red and white lights
